# Verbatim ports (PORTING.md mode `verbatim`): these must stay byte-identical
# to upstream so releases apply as diffs — `diff upstream/package/src/<f>
# src/lib/<f>` is required to be empty (CLAUDE.md non-negotiable #3). Upstream's
# 2-space/double-quote style differs from this repo's Prettier config, so we
# exclude verbatim files from Prettier rather than reformat them. ESLint still
# lints them (eslint-config-prettier disables only the stylistic rules). Add
# each new verbatim port here as it lands.
src/lib/utils/element-identification.ts
src/lib/utils/storage.ts
src/lib/utils/freeze-animations.ts
src/lib/utils/screenshot.ts
src/lib/utils/sync.ts
# `generate-output.ts` is mode `adapted` (only its import block diverges), but
# its body must stay byte-identical to upstream — `diff` of everything past the
# imports is required to be empty (issue #12) — so it is Prettier-excluded too.
src/lib/utils/generate-output.ts
# `index.ts` is mode `adapted` (drops only the `source-location` re-export): it
# must stay byte-identical to upstream's barrel except that one line so upstream
# changes to the barrel apply as a clean diff (issue #13) — so it is
# Prettier-excluded to preserve upstream's double-quote/extensionless style.
src/lib/utils/index.ts

